## Phase 7 — Security & Production Readiness

### 1. API & Websocket Security
Right now, anyone could theoretically open Postman, connect to your Socket server, and emit a fake `imposter:sabotage` event to ruin a game. 
> [!IMPORTANT]
> *Production fix:* In your socket connection logic, you must pass the JWT token and verify it before allowing the socket to connect.

### 2. Rate Limiting & Helmet
In `devception-server/src/index.ts`, you use `helmet()` (which adds secure HTTP headers to block XSS attacks) and `express-rate-limit` (which blocks IPs that make more than 200 requests per 15 minutes to prevent DDoS attacks).

### 3. XSS (Cross-Site Scripting)
Because players write code and chat, if a player types `<script>alert('hack')</script>` in the chat, and React renders it as raw HTML, they just hacked other players. React protects against this automatically by escaping text, but never use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.

