## Phase 10 — Guided Learning Roadmap

You vibe-coded an amazing architecture. Here is your path to becoming a Senior Engineer:

### 1. Stop relying on AI for the "Glue"
AI is great for writing the body of a function. You need to start writing the *connections* yourself. Next time you make a route, write the Express router, controller, and React `fetch` call by hand.

### 2. Learn System Design Concepts
Look into **Operational Transformation (OT)**. Since you built a collaborative editor, reading how OT works will blow your mind and give you massive respect in interviews.

### 3. Debugging Practice
Stop copy-pasting errors into AI.
- Use `console.log()` heavily on the backend.
- Open the Chrome Network Tab. Look at the WebSocket frames. See the actual data flowing back and forth.
- Read the stack trace. Find the exact file and line number.

### 4. Code Smells to Fix Next
- Your `Game.model.ts` is huge. In a real environment, you might abstract `Tasks` into their own MongoDB collection and reference them by ID to prevent the `Game` document from hitting the 16MB MongoDB limit.
- Start writing Unit Tests. Add `Jest` to your backend and write a test to ensure that when an Imposter calls a sabotage, the cooldown logic actually works.

